predicted heavy traffic along the desert highways, ``And remember,
all the Air Police fellows out there got radar.''
   Lovato said the worst traffic jams will occur before dawn. Haley
said all gates to Edwards Air Force Base will be closed to the
general public, and access to the east shore viewing site _ which
doesn't require a vehicle pass or entry through any of the gates _
will be halted one hour before the landing.
   ``No gasoline is available at the viewing site,'' a NASA fact
sheet advised. ``No shelter from the sun will be available. No
telephones will be available. No plumbing or electricity will be
available. No dumping facilities for RV toilets will be available.''
   However, dozens of portable, chemical toilets already have been
placed on the lakeshore viewing site. Very little water or food
will be available, so spectators are advised to bring their own.
